SPEAKER after speaker talked about acting principal Priscilla Mchunu&rsquo;s dedication to her work. She was shot dead while teaching a matric class at Laduma High School in Kwampumuza in KZN on Saturday. Speaking at the local community hall yesterday, head girl Noxolo Ngidi (17) said the school had lost a great leader. Priscilla&rsquo;s sister Zanele said her sister was the sole breadwinner. &ldquo;Her kids are traumatised. &ldquo;We can&rsquo;t find peace while her killers are still on the loose,&rdquo; she said. SGB chairman Thabiso Ndabezitha (39) said they trusted cops. &ldquo;We need peace in our hearts,&rdquo; he said. KZN education spokesman Muzi Mahlambi said Priscilla&rsquo;s murder, while working over a long weekend, showed her dedication. Cop spokeswoman Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said no arrests had yet been made. &ldquo;Anyone with information must contact cops or Crime Stop.&rdquo; Priscilla will be buried on Sunday.